Ingredient: corn on the cob, husks and silk removed
low sodium, low fat vegetable broth
skinless, boneless chicken breasts, cut into bite-sized pieces
crushed red pepper flakes, or to taste
oil-packed sun-dried tomatoes, drained and cut into strips
hamburger buns, split and lightly toasted
sweet potatoes, peeled and cut into chunks
beef flank steak, sliced 1/4 inch thick on the diagonal
pineapple - peeled, cored, and cut into 6 wedges
turkey kielbasa, cut diagonally into 1/4 inch slices
fresh sea bass, about 1 inch thick
avocado oil, or more as needed
hot pepper sauce, or to taste
seafood seasoning, such as Old Bay
red bell pepper, seeded and chopped
ground black pepper, or to taste
navy beans, soaked overnight and drained
salt and ground black pepper to taste
cucumber, peeled, cut into small strips
dry navy beans, soaked overnight or boiled for one hour
thick cut bacon, cut into 1 inch pieces
salt and ground black pepper to taste
fresh jalapeño chile pepper, finely chopped
fresh asparagus, trimmed and cut into 1 inch pieces
salt and ground black pepper to taste
chile-garlic sauce (such as Sriracha®), or to taste
whole-wheat bread, torn into small crumbs
just-ripe bananas, sliced in 1/10-inch-thick rounds, or more as needed
Golden Delicious apples, cored and thinly sliced
freshly ground black pepper to taste
